      "need to prove that $|a_{2009}| = 0$.\n\nFirst, we need to understand the recurrence relation. The relation $a_{n+2} = \\frac{a_n + a_{n+1}}{1 - a_n \\cdot a_{n+1}}$ resembles the tangent addition formula. If $a_n = \\tan(\\theta_n)$, then $\\tan(\\theta_{n+2}) = \\tan(\\theta_n + \\theta_{n+1})$.\n\nTherefore, if we let $\\theta_n = \\arctan(a_n)$, then $\\theta_{n+2} = \\theta_n + \\theta_{n+1}$.\n\nGiven $a_1 = 1$, we have $\\theta_1 = \\arctan(1) = \\frac{\\pi}{4}$.\n\nGiven $a_2 = \\frac{1}{\\sqrt{3}}$, we have $\\theta_2 = \\arctan\\left(\\frac{1}{\\sqrt{3}}\\right) = \\frac{\\pi}{6}$.\n\nThen, $\\theta_3 = \\theta_1 + \\theta_2 = \\frac{\\pi}{4} + \\frac{\\pi}{6} = \\frac{5\\pi}{12}$, so $a_3 = \\tan\\left(\\frac{5\\pi}{12}\\right)$.\n\nSimilarly, $\\theta_4 = \\theta_2 + \\theta_3 = \\frac{\\pi}{6} + \\frac{5\\pi}{12} = \\frac{7\\pi}{12}$, so $a_4 = \\tan\\left(\\frac{7\\pi}{12}\\right)$.\n\n$\\theta_5 = \\theta_3 + \\theta_4 = \\frac{5\\pi}{12} + \\frac{7\\pi}{12} = \\pi$, so $a_5 = \\tan(\\pi) = 0$.\n\n$\\theta_6 = \\theta_4 + \\theta_5 = \\frac{7\\pi}{12} + \\pi = \\frac{19\\pi}{12}$, so $a_6 = \\tan\\left(\\frac{19\\pi}{12}\\right) = \\tan\\left(\\pi + \\frac{7\\pi}{12}\\right) = \\tan\\left(\\frac{7\\pi}{12}\\right) = -2 - \\sqrt{3}$.\n\n$\\theta_7 = \\theta_5 + \\theta_6 = \\pi + \\frac{19\\pi}{12} = \\frac{31\\pi}{12}$, so $a_7 = \\tan\\left(\\frac{31\\pi}{12}\\right) = \\tan\\left(2\\pi + \\frac{7\\pi}{12}\\right) = \\tan\\left(\\frac{7\\pi}{12}\\right) = -2 - \\sqrt{3}$.\n\n$\\theta_8 = \\theta_6 + \\theta_7 = \\frac{19\\pi}{12} + \\frac{31\\pi}{12} = \\frac{50\\pi}{12} = \\frac{25\\pi}{6}$, so $a_8 = \\tan\\left(\\frac{25\\pi}{6}\\right) = \\tan\\left(4\\pi + \\frac{\\pi}{6}\\right) = \\tan\\left(\\frac{\\pi}{6}\\right) = \\frac{1}{\\sqrt{3}}$ which is the same as $a_2$.\n\nSimilarly, $\\theta_9 = \\theta_7 + \\theta_8 = \\frac{31\\pi}{12} + \\frac{25\\pi}{6} = \\frac{31\\pi + 50\\pi}{12} = \\frac{81\\pi}{12} = \\frac{27\\pi}{4}$, so $a_9 = \\tan\\left(\\frac{27\\pi}{4}\\right) = \\tan\\left(6\\pi + \\frac{3\\pi}{4}\\right) = \\tan\\left(\\frac{3\\pi}{4}\\right) = -1$ which is the same as $a_1$.\n\nTherefore, the sequence is periodic with period 12. So $a_{n + 12} = a_n$.\n\nSo $a_{2009} = a_{1 + 2008}$. Since $2008 = 12 \\cdot 167 + 4$, so $a_{2009} = a_{1 + 4} = a_5 = 0$.\n\nTherefore, $|a_{2009}| = 0$.\n\nTo prove this in Lean 4, we need to show that $a_{2009} = 0$.\n\nLet's write the proof:\n\n```tactics\nhave h3 : a 3 = (a 1 + a 2) / (1 - a 1 * a 2) := h₂ 1 (by norm_num)\nrw [h₀, h₁] at h3\n```\n\nNow we compute $a_3$:\n$a_3 = \\frac{1 + \\frac{1}{\\sqrt{3}}}{1 - 1 \\cdot \\frac{1}{\\sqrt{3}}} = \\frac{1 + \\frac{1}{\\sqrt{3}}}{1 - \\frac{1}{\\sqrt{3}}} = \\frac{\\sqrt{3} + 1}{\\sqrt{3} - 1} = \\frac{(\\sqrt{3} + 1)^2}{2} = \\frac{4 + 2\\sqrt{3}}{2} = 2 + \\sqrt{3}$\n\n```tactics\nhave ha3 : a 3 = 2 + Real.sqrt 3 := by\n  rw [h3]\n  field_simp\n  <;> nlinarith [Real.sqrt_pos.mpr (show (0 : ℝ) < (3 : ℝ) by norm_num), Real.sq_sqrt (show (0 : ℝ) ≤ (3 : ℝ) by norm_num)]\n```\n\nNow, let's compute $a_4$:\n\n```tactics\nhave h4 : a 4 = (a 2 + a 3) / (1 - a 2 * a 3) := h₂ 2 (by norm_num)\nrw [h₁, ha3] at h4\n```\n\nCompute $a_4$:\n$a_4 = \\frac{\\frac{1}{\\sqrt{3}} + (2 + \\sqrt{3})}{1 - \\frac{1}{\\sqrt{3}} \\cdot (2 + \\sqrt{3})} = \\frac{\\frac{1}{\\sqrt{3}} + 2 + \\sqrt{3}}{1 - \\frac{2 + \\sqrt{3}}{\\sqrt{3}}} = \\frac{\\frac{1 + 2\\sqrt{3} + 3}{\\sqrt{3}}}{\\frac{\\sqrt{3} - (2 + \\sqrt{3})}{\\sqrt{3}}} = \\frac{4 + 2\\sqrt{3}}{-2} = -2 - \\sqrt{3}$\n\n```tactics\nhave ha4 : a 4 = -2 - Real.sqrt 3 := by\n  rw [h4]\n  field_simp\n  <;> nlinarith [Real.sqrt_pos.mpr (show (0 : ℝ) < (3 : ℝ) by norm_num), Real.sq_sqrt (show (0 : ℝ) ≤ (3 : ℝ) by norm_num)]\n```\n\nNow, compute $a_5$:\n\n```tactics\nhave h5 : a 5 = (a 3 + a 4) / (1 - a 3 * a 4) := h₂ 3 (by norm_num)\nrw [ha3, ha4] at h5\n```\n\nCompute $a_5$:\n$a_5 = \\frac{(2 + \\sqrt{3}) + (-2 - \\sqrt{3})}{1 - (2 + \\sqrt{3})(-2 - \\sqrt{3})} = \\frac{0}{1 + 4 + 2\\sqrt{3} - 2\\sqrt{3} - 3} = \\frac{0}{2} = 0$\n\n```tactics\nhave ha5 : a 5 = 0 := by\n  rw [h5]\n  norm_num\n```\n\nNow, we can prove that $a_{n + 12} = a_n$.\n\nLet's prove the periodicity:\n\n```tactics\nhave h6 : a 6 = (a 4 + a 5) / (1 - a 4 * a 5) := h₂ 4 (by norm_num)\nrw [ha4, ha5] at h6\n```\n\nCompute $a_6$:\n$a_6 = \\frac{-2 - \\sqrt{3} + 0}{1 - (-2 - \\sqrt{3}) \\cdot 0} = -2 - \\sqrt{3}$\n\n```tactics\nhave ha6 : a 6 = -2 - Real.sqrt 3 := by\n  rw [h6]\n  norm_num\n```\n\nSimilarly, compute $a_7$:\n\n```tactics\nhave h7 : a 7 = (a 5 + a 6) / (1 - a 5 * a 6) := h₂ 5 (by norm_num)\nrw [ha5, ha6] at h7\n```\n\nCompute $a_7$:\n$a_7 = \\frac{0 + (-2 - \\sqrt{3})}{1 - 0 \\cdot (-2 - \\sqrt{3})} = -2 - \\sqrt{3}$\n\n```tactics\nhave ha7 : a 7 = -2 - Real.sqrt 3 := by\n  rw [h7]\n  norm_num\n```\n\nCompute $a_8$:\n\n```tactics\nhave h8 : a 8 = (a 6 + a 7) / (1 - a 6 * a 7) := h₂ 6 (by norm_num)\nrw [ha6, ha7] at h8\n```\n\nCompute $a_8$:\n$a_8 = \\frac{(-2 - \\sqrt{3}) + (-2 - \\sqrt{3})}{1 - (-2 - \\sqrt{3}) \\cdot (-2 - \\sqrt{3})} = \\frac{-4 - 2\\sqrt{3}}{1 - (4 + 2\\sqrt{3} + 2\\sqrt{3} + 3)} = \\frac{-4 - 2\\sqrt{3}}{1 - 7 - 4\\sqrt{3}} = \\frac{-4 - 2\\sqrt{3}}{-6 - 4\\sqrt{3}} = \\frac{2 + \\sqrt{3}}{3 + 2\\sqrt{3}} = \\frac{(2 + \\sqrt{3})(3 - 2\\sqrt{3})}{(3 + 2\\sqrt{3})(3 - 2\\sqrt{3})} = \\frac{6 - 4\\sqrt{3} + 3\\sqrt{3} - 6}{9 - 12} = \\frac{-\\sqrt{3}}{-3} = \\frac{1}{\\sqrt{3}}$\n\n```tactics\nhave ha8 : a 8 = 1 / Real.sqrt 3 := by\n  rw [h8]\n  field_simp\n  <;> nlinarith [Real.sqrt_pos.mpr (show (0 : ℝ) < (3 : ℝ) by norm_num), Real.sq_sqrt (show (0 : ℝ) ≤ (3 : ℝ) by norm_num)]\n```\n\nCompute $a_9$:\n\n```tactics\nhave h9 : a 9 = (a 7 + a 8) / (1 - a 7 * a 8) := h₂ 7 (by norm_num)\nrw [ha7, ha8] at h9\n```\n\nCompute $a_9$:\n$a_9 = \\frac{-2 - \\sqrt{3} + \\frac{1}{\\sqrt{3}}}{1 - (-2 - \\sqrt{3}) \\cdot \\frac{1}{\\sqrt{3}}}$\n\nMultiply numerator and denominator by $\\sqrt{3}$:\nNumerator: $(-2 - \\sqrt{3})\\sqrt{3} + 1 = -2\\sqrt{3} - 3 + 1 = -2\\sqrt{3} - 2$\nDenominator: $\\sqrt{3} - (-2 - \\sqrt{3}) = \\sqrt{3} + 2 + \\sqrt{3} = 2\\sqrt{3} + 2$\n\nSo $a_9 = \\frac{-2\\sqrt{3} - 2}{2\\sqrt{3} + 2} = \\frac{-2(\\sqrt{3} + 1)}{2(\\sqrt{3} + 1)} = -1$\n\n```tactics\nhave ha9 : a 9 = -1 := by\n  rw [h9]\n  field_simp\n  <;> nlinarith [Real.sqrt_pos.mpr (show (0 : ℝ) < (3 : ℝ) by norm_num), Real.sq_sqrt (show (0 : ℝ) ≤ (3 : ℝ) by norm_num)]\n```\n\nCompute $a_{10}$:\n\n```tactics\nhave h10 : a 10 = (a 8 + a 9) / (1 - a 8 * a 9) := h₂ 8 (by norm_num)\nrw [ha8, ha9] at h10\n```\n\nCompute $a_{10}$:\n$a_{10} = \\frac{\\frac{1}{\\sqrt{3}} + (-1)}{1 - \\frac{1}{\\sqrt{3}} \\cdot (-1)} = \\frac{\\frac{1}{\\sqrt{3}} - 1}{1 + \\frac{1}{\\sqrt{3}}} = \\frac{1 - \\sqrt{3}}{1 + \\sqrt{3}} = \\frac{(1 - \\sqrt{3})^2}{2} = \\frac{1 - 2\\sqrt{3} + 3}{2} = \\frac{4 - 2\\sqrt{3}}{2} = 2 - \\sqrt{3}$\n\n```tactics\nhave ha10 : a 10 = 2 - Real.sqrt 3 := by\n  rw [h10]\n  field_simp\n  <;> nlinarith [Real.sqrt_pos.mpr (show (0 : ℝ) < (3 : ℝ) by norm_num), Real.sq_sqrt (show (0 : ℝ) ≤ (3 : ℝ) by norm_num)]\n```\n\nCompute $a_{11}$:\n\n```tactics\nhave h11 : a 11 = (a 9 + a 10) / (1 - a 9 * a 10) := h₂ 9 (by norm_num)\nrw [ha9, ha10] at h11\n```\n\nCompute $a_{11}$:\n$a_{11} = \\frac{-1 + (2 - \\sqrt{3})}{1 - (-1)(2 - \\sqrt{3})} = \\frac{1 - \\sqrt{3}}{1 + 2 - \\sqrt{3}} = \\frac{1 - \\sqrt{3}}{3 - \\sqrt{3}} = \\frac{(1 - \\sqrt{3})(3 + \\sqrt{3})}{(3 - \\sqrt{3})(3 + \\sqrt{3})} = \\frac{3 + \\sqrt{3} - 3\\sqrt{3} - 3}{6} = \\frac{-2\\sqrt{3}}{6} = -\\frac{\\sqrt{3}}{3}$\n\n```tactics\nhave ha11 : a 11 = -Real.sqrt 3 / 3 := by\n  rw [h11]\n  field_simp\n  <;> nlinarith [Real.sqrt_pos.mpr (show (0 : ℝ) < (3 : ℝ) by norm_num), Real.sq_sqrt (show (0 : ℝ) ≤ (3 : ℝ) by norm_num)]\n```\n\nCompute $a_{12}$:\n\n```tactics\nhave h12 : a 12 = (a 10 + a 11) / (1 - a 10 * a 11) := h₂ 10 (by norm_num)\nrw [ha10, ha11] at h12\n```\n\nCompute $a_{12}$:\n$a_{12} = \\frac{(2 - \\sqrt{3}) + (-\\frac{\\sqrt{3}}{3})}{1 - (2 - \\