      "\n```\n\nWe need to prove $|a_{2009}| = 0$, i.e., $a_{2009} = 0$.\n\nLet's compute the first few terms to find a cycle:\n- $a_1 = 1$\n- $a_2 = \\frac{1}{\\sqrt{3}}$\n- $a_3 = 2 + \\sqrt{3}$\n- $a_4 = -2 - \\sqrt{3}$\n- $a_5 = 0$\n- $a_6 = -2 - \\sqrt{3}$\n- $a_7 = \\frac{\\sqrt{3}}{3}$\n- $a_8 = 2 + \\sqrt{3}$\n- $a_9 = 0$\n\nWe observe a cycle of length 4: $0, -2 - \\sqrt{3}, \\frac{\\sqrt{3}}{3}, 2 + \\sqrt{3}$\n\nTherefore, $a_{4k+1} = 0$ for $k \\geq 1$.\n\nSince $2009 = 4 \\cdot 502 + 1$, $a_{2009} = 0$.\n\nLet's try to write the proof in Lean 4.\n\n```tactics\nhave h3 : a 3 = 2 + Real.sqrt 3 := by \n  specialize h₂ 1 (by norm_num)\n  rw [h₀, h₁] at h₂\n  have h4 : Real.sqrt 3 > 0 := by positivity\n  field_simp [(show Real.sqrt 3 ≠ 0 by positivity)] at h₂ ⊢\n  nlinarith [Real.sqrt_pos.mpr (show (3 : ℝ) > 0 by norm_num), Real.sq_sqrt (show (0 : ℝ) ≤ (3 : ℝ) by norm_num)]\n```\n\nNow we have $a_3 = 2 + \\sqrt{3}$.\n\nLet's compute $a_4$:\n$$a_4 = \\frac{a_2 + a_3}{1 - a_2 \\cdot a_3} = \\frac{\\frac{1}{\\sqrt{3}} + (2 + \\sqrt{3})}{1 - \\frac{1}{\\sqrt{3}} \\cdot (2 + \\sqrt{3})} = -2 - \\sqrt{3}$$\n\n```tactics\nhave h4 : a 4 = -2 - Real.sqrt 3 := by \n  specialize h₂ 2 (by norm_num)\n  rw [h₁, h3] at h₂\n  have h5 : Real.sqrt 3 > 0 := by positivity\n  field_simp [(show Real.sqrt 3 ≠ 0 by positivity)] at h₂ ⊢\n  nlinarith [Real.sqrt_pos.mpr (show (3 : ℝ) > 0 by norm_num), Real.sq_sqrt (show (0 : ℝ) ≤ (3 : ℝ) by norm_num)]\n```\n\nNow we compute $a_5$:\n$$a_5 = \\frac{a_3 + a_4}{1 - a_3 \\cdot a_4} = \\frac{(2 + \\sqrt{3}) + (-2 - \\sqrt{3})}{1 - (2 + \\sqrt{3})(-2 - \\sqrt{3})} = \\frac{0}{1 + (2 + \\sqrt{3})^2} = 0$$\n\n```tactics\nhave h5 : a 5 = 0 := by \n  specialize h₂ 3 (by norm_num)\n  rw [h3, h4] at h₂\n  norm_num [h₂]\n```\n\nNow we compute $a_6$:\n$$a_6 = \\frac{a_4 + a_5}{1 - a_4 \\cdot a_5} = \\frac{(-2 - \\sqrt{3}) + 0}{1 - 0} = -2 - \\sqrt{3}$$\n\n```tactics\nhave h6 : a 6 = -2 - Real.sqrt 3 := by \n  specialize h₂ 4 (by norm_num)\n  rw [h4,